<TITLE>
ABOUT PULSE OF THE PLANET
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#E9C2A6">
<IMG SRC="pulse.gif"
                                HEIGHT=110
                                WIDTH=100
                                BORDER=5
                                ALIGN=LEFT
                                HSPACE=10
                                VSPACE=10
                                ALT="PULSE OF THE PLANET">
<FONT SIZE=6>
About <b>Pulse of the Planet</b>
</FONT>
<BR>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE=4>
<P>
Each weekday, <b>Pulse of the Planet</b> brings the human face of technology into the lives of more than a million listeners around the world, blending interviews with scientists together with the sounds of innovation in action.
<P>
<IMG SRC="jim2a.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>

Executive Producer Jim  Metzner has produced more than 2,000 short-format radio programs since 1979, winning over a dozen broadcasting awards, including the 1995 Grand Award at the International Radio Festival of New York.<P>

<b>Pulse of the Planet</b> is heard on more than 200 public and commercial
stations in the United States, and over the Voice of America and the Armed Forces Radio Network.
<P>
For the address of the station nearest you that broadcasts <b>Pulse of the Planet</b> contact
 <A HREF="mailto:pulseinfo@aol.com">Rob Drucker</A> at MediaAmerica Inc. 
<P>
Stations interested in broadcasting Pulse of the Planet should contact <A HREF="mailto:pulseinfo@aol.com">Rob Drucker</A> at MediaAmerica Inc., 11 West 42nd St., New York, NY, 10036; (212) 302-1100, or <A HREF="mailto:murraystreet@mcimail.com">Rob Grader</A> at Murray Street Enterprises, 69 Murray Street, New York, NY, 10007; (212) 619-1475.<P>

If you have any questions or comments about the series, email <A HREF="mailto:pulse@igc.apc.org">Jim Metzner</A>. Our mailing address is P.O. Box 22, Croton-on-Hudson, NY, 10520.

</FONT>
