<H3>Program #1344</H3>

  

<CENTER>COMPUTER VIRUSES -- The Virus Hunters</CENTER>

At this very moment, computer viruses are lurking, waiting to be downloaded into unsuspecting PCs.  But not to worry; virus hunters are hard at work, learning how to conquer infections from the inside out.  I'm Jim Metzner, and this is the Pulse of the Planet.<P>

<B>ambience</B> Virus Conversation<P>

That's Jeffrey Kephart and David Chess, two scientists at the IBM Research Center, analyzing a new computer virus.  They're picking it apart, trying to learn exactly how it works, and how to control it.<P> 

"It's more like solving a crossword puzzle, I think.  You have a thing sitting there and you have to figure out how it hangs together, how parts of it relate to other parts, what it's doing, what's behind it."<P>

Mr. Chess and Mr. Kephart are part of a defense team trying to prevent worldwide virus infection.  Once they have a virus deciphered, they send programmed disinfection for it all over the globe, to prevent future outbreaks.  Soon, they hope to develop an automatic computer system that'll analyze and remove viruses without their help.  But, in the meantime, the human defense team is doing very well on its own.<P>

"The world of computers is a manmade world.  So we have a much better chance of being able to devise cures for computer viruses.  There isn't any virus that has ever been created so far that has presented that much of a difficulty for people like Dave."<P>

"I think part of the perception is that at least some parts of the public think that these must be sort of super genius programmers doing these things.  I think that's not true at all.  Writing a virus is not difficult.  Viruses are very simple programs.  All they do is read other programs, write to them, they do nothing that requires any particular skill in anything to code.  Millions of people have the capability of writing viruses and we're just happy that as few as several hundred actually do it."<P>

Pulse of the Planet is presented by DuPont, makers of better things of better living.<P>

