<HTML><TITLE>1331</TITLE>

<H3>Program #1331</H3>

  

<CENTER>WIRELESS SUBWAY SPEAKERS</CENTER>

<B>ambience</B> Subway Station<P>
<B>FX</B> Garbled Subway Announcement<P>
If youve ever been in a subway station, youve heard announcements like that.  But thanks to a new wireless public address system, we may be able to look forward to understandable subway messages.  I'm Jim Metzner, and this is the Pulse of the Planet.<P>

"The system we have designed is called WAVES, which stands for Wireless Audio Visual and Emergency System."<P>

Dr. Alan Avidan is the Executive Vice President of the MadahCom Corporation, where they've developed a public address system that uses digital technology to deliver clearer messages than traditional PA systems.<P>

"Public address announcements in general sound unintelligible because the analog signal degrades along the wire and picks up interference and hum.  What makes the problem worse is that speakers are often placed where the wires are, and not where the sound is best.  The WAVES system solves this problem, because it's wireless, which means that you can place the speakers where the sound is best, and it's digital so that the signal doesn't degrade and the output is clean and clear without any interference."<P>

Using special radio signals, a WAVES transmitter sends announcements to receivers attached to speakers throughout the station.<P>

"The WAVES system uses state of the art digital radio, that converts voice and music into a data stream, and sends it via radio signal.  It's a frequency hopping system, which means that all the WAVES units change frequencies hundreds of times a second.  You can avoid any interference that's out there by skipping channels that have interference in them."<P>

So instead of hearing:<P>
<B>FX</B> Garbled Subway Transfer Announcement<P>

You'll now hear:<P>
<B>FX</B> WAVES Announcement "This is 59th Street, Columbus Circle.  Transfer here for the A, C, B, D, 1 or the 9 train."<P>

Pulse of the Planet is presented by DuPont, makers of better things for better living.<P>

