<HTML><TITLE>1306</TITLE>

<H3>Program #1306</H3>

  

<CENTER>KINETIC TENNIS RACKET</CENTER>

A newly designed tennis racket not only helps prevent tennis elbow, it can actually improve your game. I'm Jim Metzner, and this is the Pulse of the Planet.<P>

Kevin Gilbert is president of the ProKennex Company.<P>

"This idea came from an aerospace engineer out of Germany, who had a friend who had tennis elbow.  His friend came to him and asked him if scientists had a way to eliminate the shock and vibration that he assumed was creating this tennis elbow.  At the time, Roland Summer had worked on reducing shock and vibration in airplane wings, using a basic technology that incorporated movable mass in the wings.  He applied this technology in a crude way to a tennis racket and, voila, the friend was able to play tennis again without the pain of tennis elbow.  That's really where the idea began."<P>

Prokennex took Summer's prototype and developed it into the Kinetic tennis racket.<P>

"The Kinetic racket from the outside looks like any other technical, high quality racket.  Unlike any other racket, inside the hoop of the frame you've got a hundred chambers or capsules, and inside each capsule you have a precise amount of what we call kinetic mass, which is really small lead microbearings.  These are free moving, so when you begin to swing the racket, these microbearings move to the back of the chamber.  When the racket meets the tennis ball, it releases all one hundred chambers of kinetic mass, so now all of these microbearings are all moving forward.  So not only do you get the momentum of the frame itself, but you get the momentum of these hundred chambers of kinetic mass to add their energy to the ball.  So, in essence, more stability, less shock, and less vibration.  So you're going to hit better shots, more often, with less effort, and no pain."<P>

Pulse of the Planet is presented by DuPont, makers of better things for better living.<P>

