<HTML><TITLE>1264</TITLE>

<H3>Program #1264</H3>

  

<CENTER>U.S. FIRST - The Mission</CENTER>

Do you think a crowd of people could get as excited about science as they do at a 
pro sports event? Well, an organization called U.S. FIRST is working on it. I'm Jim 
Metzner, and this is the Pulse of the Planet.<p>

<B>ambience</B> 1995 competition, starting countdown  <p>

"U.S. FIRST has as its prime mission to show everybody, but particularly kids that science and technology is fun, it's accessible, it's rewarding, and it's for everybody."  <p>

Dean Kamen is a physicist, engineer, inventor and the founder of U.S. FIRST.<p>

<B>ambience</B> Boomer  <p>

And that's Boomer, one of the prototype robots for the 1996 U.S. FIRST competition. The event teams engineers with young people to build robots to compete in a kind of science Super Bowl.<p>

"We said, let's steal from the playbooks of sports and put in front of kids the NFL of smarts, and just as little kids aren't induced to play football by watching other little kids play, they like to see the best 200 atheletes in the world do it, we said let's go to the best companies in the world, and find the best technologists in the world, and put them on center stage for these kids, let's let the kids participate with them in exciting projects, in inventing and creating robots that can go and compete in an event that's as exciting as any other other sporting event, and that's what our competition's all about."  <p>

"What I think this country really needs is an awareness, particularly by young kids, that it's fun. Because no matter how much you change the curriculum, when a third of the kids in the major cities are dropping out of high school, no matter what you change on the supply side, if there's no fundamental demand for excellence in science and technology like there is for instance in sports, we're not going to be competitive.  A little bit of desire is worth a whole lot of opportunity." <p> 

<B>ambience</B> 1995 competition, ending countdown  <p>

Pulse of the Planet is presented by DuPont, makers of better things for better 
living. <p>

