<TITLE>1168</TITLE>

<H3>Program #1168</H3><P>

<CENTER>CONTRACEPTIVE VACCINE - A More Natural Process</CENTER><P>

<B>music</B><BR>
Scientists are developing a new form of contraception that doesn't use hormones, has no known side effects, and is administered once every eight to twelve months. I'm Jim Metzner and this is the Pulse of the Planet.<P>

238) "A number of years ago, we discovered a unique protein that was associated with the sperm cell. Since it was a unique protein, we knew that it would stimulate an immune response. And we knew furthermore that naturally-occuring infertility due to an immune response, caused problems in couples who wanted to bear children. So, drawing upon that experiment of nature, we thought that perhaps we could develop our finding into a practical contraceptive approach that would be different and useful."<P>

Dr. Erwin Goldberg, professor of Biochemistry at Northwestern University, is developing a vaccine against pregnancy. He says that injecting the unique sperm protein into a female's bloodstream, causes her immune system to produce antibodies to fight off the foreign invader. If she's exposed to sperm later on, these antibodies attack and kill them before they can reach the egg.<P>

154) "We would anticipate no safety problems because the vaccine is developed as a normal process in the body against a foreign substance. This happens all the time and does not create any health problems. And, in fact, there are examples of not only women, but men also who have antibodies in their body. They're infertile as a consequence of these antibodies against sperm, and yet they're perfectly healthy in all other respects."<P>

Dr. Goldberg also says the contraceptive wears off after about eight months.
Pulse of the Planet is presented by DuPont to recognize the role of research and technology in our daily lives.<P>
<B>music</B><P>

</HTML>
