<head>
<title>About Keith Medcalf & Associates</title>
<base href="http://www.dessus.com/about.html">
</head>

<body background=/icons/backgr/paper10.gif text=0x000000>
<center>
<h1>About Keith Medcalf & Associates</h1>
</center>

<p>
<b>Keith Medcalf and Associates</b> is a Consulting Company located in
Toronto, Ontario, Canada, specializing in OS/2, NT, DOS, and Windows; with
particular emphasis on Local and Wide Area Networking (LAN and WAN),
Database Systems, Internet Connectivity and, Client/Server information
systems.  Keith Medcalf and Associates is an IBM BESTeam Member.
</p>

<p>
<b>Keith Medcalf and Associates</b> <i>(dessus.com)</i> is running on an
Intel 80486dx33 processor with 32MB of RAM and total of 3 GB of disk
space spread over a 560 MB Samsung IDE drive, an IBM 1.02 GB IDE drive,
a Fujitsu 1 GB SCSI-2, and a Fujitsu 520 MB SCSI-2 Drive.  A NEC 2x
CD-ROM drive is also connected. The Operating System is IBM
<a href=http://www.austin.ibm.com/pspinfo/os2.html>OS/2</a>
Warp Server. The connection to the internet is provided by
<a href=http://www.io.org/>Internex Online</a>;
over the Stentor Microlink
<a href=http://www.stentor.ca/basie/products/isdn/isdn.html>ISDN</a>
service.  An
<a href=//www.ascend.com/>Ascend Pipeline 50</a>
is providing routing on this network and is calling into an Ascend Max 4000
at
<a href=//www.ican.ca/>Internet Canada</a>.
</p>

<h2>Facilities</h2>

<p>
Facilities available from this server include a full range of base
services, including FTP, WWW, and SMTP mail.

<hr>

<p>
Please send any updates, corrections, or additions to the Web Master,
email: <A HREF=mailto:kmedcalf@dessus.com> Keith Medcalf</A>
