<html>
<head>
<title>ISDN Connectivity in Toronto (Ontario/Canada)</title>
<base href="http://www.dessus.com/isdn/index.html">
</head>

<body background=/icons/backgr/paper10.gif text=0x000000>
<center><h1>ISDN Connectivity in Toronto (Ontario/Canada)</h1></center>
<p>

<p>
Ordering an ISDN line in Toronto (sold under the trade name of MicroLink
for standard BRI (2B+D) access) was relatively straight forward.
Installation was quick and easy, and the installer great.  Total time
from ordering to completed installation:  one week!  The default
configuration which Bell puts on the line works flawlessly and is in
fact the provisioning setup required by many simpler TA's.  You only
need to specify how to provision the line if you want features such as
ETKS or CACH enabled (but you will need to speak to an Engineer to get
advanced ISDN features).  The default provisioning is voice+data on any
channel, DMS100 Custom PVC-1 with NI-1 compatibility.
</p>

<p>
Residential Rate ISDN is now available in Ontario and Quebec (Bell
Territories) and is somewhat cheaper than Business class Microlink
service.  However, the residential service also has usage charges of
$1.00 per Bearer Channel per hour for usage during the hours from 7a-7p
Business days (M-F excl Holidays). There is a maximum usage charge cap,
however, which brings the total cost of the Residential service to max
at just a few dollars more than the business service.  The residential
service, however, is Centrex facility blocked, meaning that you cannot
get Centrex services.
</p>

<h2>Detailed Charges for Toronto (Rate Group 15)</h2>


<h3>MicroLink (Business Class) Service</h3>

<center><table border=3 width=80%>
<tr><td>Installation and Configuration, per 2B+D BRI</td><td align=right>209.00</td><td>Service Charge</td></tr>
<tr><td>Switch Termination, per 2B+D</td><td align=right>78.00</td><td>Monthly Charge</td></tr>
<tr><td>911 Location Service, per B</td><td align=right>0.32</td><td>Monthly Charge</td></tr>
<tr><td>PSTN Interconnection, each of first 5</td><td align=right>13.15</td><td>Monthly Charge</td></tr>
<tr><td>PSTN Interconnection, each of next 6</td><td align=right>37.45</td><td>Monthly Charge</td></tr>
<tr><td>PSTN Interconnection, remainder</td><td align=right>46.95</td><td>Monthly Charge</td></tr>
</table></center>
<p>
The calculation rules and conditions are as follows:
</p>
<ol>
 <li>Switch Termination is per BRI (2B+D) interface.
 <li>PSTN interconnection counts are determined by customer location
     and telephone company switch.  That is, the count is distinct for
     each combination of switch and location.
 <li>911 Location service is required on every Bearer channel, even if
     it cannot be used for Voice Bearer calls (CRTC Regulation)
 <li>Each combination of Switch and Location must purchase a minimum
     of one (1) PSTN interconnection.
 <li>The default installation configuration for BRI is 2B+D, single
     interface, and one PSTN interconnection.  Additional BRI interfaces
     to the same location from the same switch do not require PSTN and
     will not be configured for PSTN unless requested.
 <li>DSN does not presently have interconnect charges.
 <li>Features such as Equivalency are free, but must be ordered at the
     time the service is installed.  Configuration change orders carry
     a $60.00 service charge.
</ol>

<h3>MicroLink (Residential Class) Service</h3>

<center><table border=3 width=80%>
<tr><td>Installation and Configuration, per 2B+D BRI</td><td align=right>109.00</td><td>Service Charge*</td></tr>
<tr><td>Switch Termination, per 2B+D</td><td align=right>55.00</td><td>Monthly Charge</td></tr>
<tr><td>Usage / Channel / Hours**</td><td align=right>1.00</td><td><Monthly Charge</td></tr>
</table></center>
<p>
The calculation rules and conditions are as follows:
</p>
<ol>
 <li>One PSTN interconnection is included in the basic rate.  No tarrif
     is available for additional PSTNs.  Centrex services are NOT
     available for residential service.
 <li>*The installation fee is waived during the month of February
 <li>**Usage charges apply per B channel at $1.00 hour from 7a-7p
       business days.  These charges will not go into effect until
       March 1/95.
</ol>
<hr>
Please send any updates, corrections, or additions to the Web Master,
email: <A HREF=mailto:kmedcalf@zealot.dessus.com> Keith Medcalf</A><P>
</body>
