<head>
<title>OS/2 Warp FixPack and Fixes Directory</title>
<base href="http://www.dessus.com/fixpack.html">
</head>

<body background=/icons/backgr/paper10.gif text=0x000000>
<img src=/icons/misc/poweros2.gif align=right>
<h1>OS/2 Warp FixPack and Fixes Directory</h1>

<p>
The files listed here are the latest OS/2 WARP FixPack, Test Fixes, and
Final Fixes that you will need to run a totally stable Warp based system.
Not all of the references below will come from this server, however most
of them do.  Since they are FTP references, they will observe the login
quotas on my FTP server to ensure that adequate bandwidth is available
for all downloaders.
</p>

<p>
The <a href=http://www.cincyteamos2.org/>Cincinatti TeamOS/2</a>
and CPUG Users Group has a wonderful collection of OS/2 WARP
<a href=http://www.cincyteamos2.org/masterupdate.html>Master Updates</a>!
Check it out!
</p>

<center>
<table CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=2>
<tr>
 <td><a href=ftp://www.dessus.com/fixpack/fixpk26>FixPack Directory - Warp v3 FixPack 26</a>
 <td>CID or Diskette Install Ready FixPack #26
<tr>
 <td><a href=ftp://www.dessus.com/incoming/db2/>DB2/2 Fixpack 8090 Directory</a>
 <td>ZIP Files of the Individual Disks of DB2/2 Fixpack US8090
