<HTML>
<TITLE>DB2 WWW Connection URL Search Demo</TITLE>
<img src="/icons/head1.gif">   
<body>
<H1>Welcome to the DB2 WWW Connection URL Search Demo</H1>
<P>
This demonstration shows how to use DB2 WWW Connection to manage
a Uniform Resource Locator (URL) database.
You can add (insert), update, delete, and query URLs in a local
database.
If you query a set of URLs, each queried
URL will be an active link.  That is, you will be able to jump to
the page specified by the URL by selecting it.
<HR>
<P>
Please choose one of the following: 
<P>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="/cgi-bin/db2www.exe/urlquery.d2w/input">Query/Update/Delete Existing URLs</A>
<P>
<LI> <A HREF="/cgi-bin/db2www.exe/urladd.d2w/input">Add a New URL</A>
</UL>
<P>
<hr>
<p>
Other pages of interest:
<P>
<A href="celdemo.htm">DB2 WWW Connection Demonstrations</A>
<br>
<A href="http://www.software.ibm.com/data/db2/db2wfac2.html">DB2 WWW Connection Home Page</A>
<P>
<hr> 
<b>
[
<a href="http://www.ibm.com/">IBM home page</a> |
