<H1><A NAME="HDRPRT" HREF="icswgmst.html#ToC_513">Protecting your server</A></H1>
<P>
You announce to the world that you want people to come look at the
documents on your server.
But once you publicize your server to the Internet, you risk
attracting unwanted attention to the system on which it runs.
Unauthorized people may try to guess passwords, update files, execute
files, or tap into confidential data.
This chapter describes how to protect your server.
<P>
<P>Partial Table-of-Contents
<MENU>
