<TITLE>NORTH TEMPERATE LAKES LTER</TITLE>

<body background="fish6.gif" TEXT="#ffffff" VLINK="#cde2e7" LINK="#dfdf93">

<FONT SIZE="-4">This page looks best with Netscape </FONT>

<IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="gr_bar.gif">

<CENTER><H1>NORTH TEMPERATE LAKES LTER</H1></CENTER><P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="lake.gif"><P></CENTER>

<B>Welcome to the North Temperate Lakes Long-Term Ecological Research (NTL-LTER) site home page.  This page is meant to provide scientists and the general public with NTL-LTER site information and rapid access to our online datasets.  The National Science Foundation established the LTER Program to support research on long-term ecological phenomena in the United States.  We have <A HREF="sitemap.html"><B>two study regions in Wisconsin</B></A>:  the Trout Lake Region located near Boulder Junction and the Madison Lakes Region located near Madison.  These regions encompass a wide range of northern temperate lakes in glacial landscapes in urban, agricultural and forested watersheds.  Within each region, we consider a suite of adjacent lakes that share a common climate but differ dramatically in their physical, chemical, and biological characteristics. We employ a long-term perspective that permits us to examine both spatial and temporal variability and to evaluate the implications of such variability for community and ecosystem processes.  </B> 
<P>

<IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="gr_bar.gif">


<H2>Links Within the NTL-LTER Site:</H2>

<UL><A HREF="ntlsite.html"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> About the North Temperate Lakes LTER</b></A><P>

<A HREF="lter_lake.html"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> Characteristics of Primary Study Lakes</b></A><P>

<A HREF="proposal.html"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> Proposals to NSF </b></A><P>

<A HREF="gopher://limnosun.limnology.wisc.edu:70/1/lter_personnel"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> Personnel Directory</b></A><P>

<A HREF="gopher://limnosun.limnology.wisc.edu:70/11/publications"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> Publications 
</b></A><P>
<A HREF="cgi-bin/bibliography.cgi"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> New Highly Searchable Bibliography</b></A><P>

<!--<A HREF="climate.html"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><b> New interface to Trout Lake meteorological data</b></A><P>-->

<A HREF="diverse.html"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="grenbull.gif"><B> Biodiversity and Species Lists</B></A><P>

